	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=146813><span id=Scholar>Thilindi</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>29 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.78]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>In responce to several different posts:<br><br>First, here in the effect so you do not need to click on it to see it...<br><br>Description: <br>1: Increases spell effectiveness up to 23%<br>2: Restriction: Spells level 65 and lower<br>3: Restriction: Only applies to 'Hit Points (HP)' spells<br>4: Restriction: Affects 'Instant' spells only<br>5: Restriction: 'Detrimental' spells only<br>6: Restriction: 'Location Based AoE' spells excluded<br>7: Restriction: 'Point Blank AoE' spells excluded<br>8: Restriction: 'Target Based AoE' spells excluded<br>9: Restriction: 'Giants' spells excluded<br>10: Restriction: 'Dragons' spells excluded<br>11: Restriction Attribute: 87 (1)<br> <br>Details: <br>Casting Time: Instant<br>Recast Time: 0 seconds<br>Skill: Conjuration<br>Allowed Targets: Self<br>Resist: None <br>Range to target: 100<br> <br><br><br>There is no mention of a limitation to magic based spells.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is the interpretation of the spell effect:<br><br>Its a self only buff which increases the damage output on single target DD spells of level 65 and lower.  The percentage increase of damage is 23%.  For example, The wizard spell Sunstrike does 1615 hp of damage when unresisted.  With this spell in effect, it would do 1986 hp of damage unresisted.<br><br>This is very much akin to the Improved Damage line of focus effect items with the additional restriction to single target only spells.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
